  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Financial and Sustainable Development of the Legal Assistance Trust</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LAT&apos;s strategy is to achieve its vision and fulfil its mission by fundraising, networking and raising awareness in the UK so those in need in South Africa benefit from improved social development and economic rights. While over &#xA3;7m has been sent to the LRC in South Africa over the past 23 years the LAT, a small tightly-run trust, is acutely aware of its shortcomings and the need to tackle a range of organisational issues. The Board needs to be re-invigorated to play an informed, dynamic role. As we move, with LRC, to understanding what is needed for our organisations to effectively support development we need to identify and fill skills gaps at Board and operational level. We need to develop and implement a strategy, prioritised to see us through a period of transition, from at present a long-serving Chair being voluntary Director. To become more sustainable we will need to raise additional funds for adminstration purposes; also for training, in fundraising; M&amp;E; networking and fundraising events; and to learn from others so that we and the LRC may benefit. This OD planning grant will allow LAT to undertake a thorough self-assessment, develop a plan, and a training needs analysis.</narrative>
  </description>
